class.description:
The [code]GDLlama[/code] node allows you to perform complex AI text generation tasks directly from GDScript or C# without halting your game. [b]Getting Started:[/b] 1) Add a [code]GDLlama[/code] node to your scene. 2) Set the [member model_path] property to your desired, llama-compatible model. 3) Reference the node and call [method load_model] to load the model into memory. 4) You can now call generation methods like [method generate_chat_async] and connect to its signals to receive the results. 5) Unload the model using [method unload_model] when you are finished. [b]Example Usage:[/b] [codeblocks] [gdscript] @onready var llm: GDLlama = $GDLlama var full_response: String = ""
func _ready(): llm.generate_text_updated.connect(_on_text_updated) llm.generate_text_finished.connect(_on_text_finished) llm.model_path = "res://models/your_model.gguf"
if not llm.is_model_loaded(): var error = llm.load_model() if error != OK: return
var prompt = "Tell me a story about the river of Saskatoon." llm.generate_text_async(prompt) await llm.generate_text_finished llm.unload_model()
func _on_text_updated(new_text: String): full_response += new_text prints(new_text)
func _on_text_finished(full_text: String): print(full_text) [/gdscript] [/codeblocks]
